significant cell at the TOS. It is trivial to convert an unsigned single to
a double: simply push a @code{0} onto the TOS. Since numbers are represented
by Gforth using 2's complement arithmetic, converting a signed single to a
(signed) double requires sign-extension across the most significant
cell. This can be achieved using @code{s>d}. The moral of the story is that
you cannot convert a number without knowing whether it represents an
unsigned or a signed number.

