definition.



The performance advantage does not extend to using @code{noname} with the
defining word.  Therefore we also have

@findex noname-from ( @var{ xt --   } ) gforth-1.0
@cindex @code{noname-from}
@kindex noname-from
@format
@code{noname-from} ( @i{xt --  }) gforth-1.0 ``noname-from''
@end format
Create a nameless word that behaves like @i{xt}, but with an empty body.
@i{xt} must be the nt of a nameless word.



Here's a usage example:

@example
``fvalue-prototype noname create-from
latestnt constant noname-fvalue-prototype

: noname-fvalue ( r -- xt ; xt execution: -- r )
  noname-fvalue-prototype noname-from f,
  latestxt ;
@end example


